      <h2>Who We Serve</h2>
      
      <p>SPC serves students ages 5 to 21 that are not able to appropriately access education and/or important socio-emotional skills in traditional educational settings.</p>
      
      <p>Our students may be diagnosed with Autism Spectrum Disorder  among other related developmental disabilities.</p>

      <p>We might be a right fit for your child if he/she  has difficulty with one or more of the following areas:</p>
      
      <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Communication</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Making sense of gestures and words</li>
                <li>Non-verbal or lacks language to communicate effectively</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Cognitive Ability and Academic Skills</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Learning new skills</li>
                <li>Learns concepts but not able to apply them in different or new ways in the real world</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Sensory Processing and Regulation</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Remaining calm and/or reacting adversely to sound, lights, touch or other sensory inputs</li>
                <li>Getting stimulated enough to carry out a task or remaining attentive</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Behavior</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Accepting and/or understanding discipline</li>
                <li>Aggressive or self injurious behavior</li>
                <li>Repetitive or self-stimulatory behavior</li>
                <li>Difficulty with age-appropriate social skills</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Independence</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Getting basic needs met (dressing, grooming, feeding, toileting etc.)</li>
                <li>Needs support for most daily activities </li>
                <li>Lacks preferred or independent activities</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Building Relationships</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Interacting with caregivers and peers</li>
                <li>Initiating an interaction or  sustaining eye contact</li>
                <li>Establishing friendships</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Motor Planning</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Clumsy or fearful movements</li>
                <li>Effectively plan to complete motor activities</li>
                <li>Imitate movements or gestures</li>
                <li>Poor fine and gross motor skills </li>
                <li>Following multi-step instructions</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Enjoyment, Well Being and Self-Esteem</td>
            <td>
              <ul>
                <li>Understanding and expressing emotions</li>
                <li>Rigid or routinistic</li>
                <li>Anxious or uninterested</li>
                <li>Does not show enjoyment in school or at home</li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

